{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "15", "m": "04", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "10", "M": "50", "S": "38"}}, "news": [{"title": "Behind the society gates lies India\u2019s most valuable real estate story", "para": "In India, the trend of affluent consumers gravitating towards gated communities is on the rise. These self-sustained neighborhoods are not just residential areas; they are becoming vibrant economic hubs. By 2031, it's estimated that close to half of households in leading cities will call these structured environments home.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/blog/behind-the-society-gates-lies-indias-most-valuable-real-estate-story/130279741?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-221323/130279741.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "behind-the-society-gates-lies-indias-most-valuable-real-estate-story"}, {"title": "Adrianse rebrands as Design Alphabet, signalling a new era of integrated design", "para": "Adrianse has transformed into Design Alphabet, a bold rebranding that emphasizes the integral role of architecture in their progressive design philosophy. As the studio broadens its international footprint into the realms of commercial, healthcare, education, and research and development, Design Alphabet seamlessly merges architecture, interiors, and technology to enhance project clarity and execution.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/brand-connect-initiative/adrianse-rebrands-as-design-alphabet-signalling-a-new-era-of-integrated-design/130280222?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-171230/130280222.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "brand-connect-initiative"}, {"title": "Ludhiana improvement trust organises draw of lots for 179 Atal Apartment flats", "para": "Ludhiana Improvement Trust held a Baisakhi draw for 179 Atal Apartment flats, with Local Bodies Minister Sanjeev Arora present. Successful allottees were assured possession by year-end, as construction progresses rapidly. LIT also plans new affordable housing and commercial projects, with the government promising future schemes for those who missed out.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/ludhiana-improvement-trust-conducts-draw-for-atal-apartment-flats-on-baisakhi/130279438?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-145801/130279438.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}]}